
[1]adjective

   AD'JECTIVE, n. In grammar, a word used with a noun, to express a
   quality of the thing named, or something attributed to it, or to limit
   or define it, or to specify or describe a thing, as distinct from
   something else. It is called also an attributive or attribute. Thus, in
   the phrase, a wise ruler, wise is the adjective or attribute,
   expressing a particular property of ruler.
